        "Abstract": "Hate speech detection is a challenging problem with most of the datasets available in only one language: English. In this paper, we conduct a large-scale analysis of multilingual hate speech in 9 languages from 16 different sources. We observe that in low-resource settings, simple models such as LASER embedding with logistic regression perform the best, while in high-resource settings, BERT-based models perform better. Our proposed framework could be used as an efficient solution for low-resource languages. These models could also act as good baselines for future multilingual hate speech detection tasks."
